{"lemma":"مَلّاحُو","slug":"مَلّاحُو","root":"م.ل.ح","root_slug":"م-ل-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/م-ل-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38879","n38883","n38884"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%AD%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mariner, shipman, sailor, helmsman"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"seepweed (Suaeda spp.)","tags":["regional"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thickened basic stew"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of مِلْح (milḥ)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"masculine plural of مَلِيح (malīḥ)","tags":["form-of","masculine","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic מַלָּחָא (mallāḥā) / ܡܰܠܴܚܳܐ (mallāḥā, “shipman, sailor”), from Akkadian 𒈣𒁻 (malāḫum, “shipman, sailor”), from Sumerian 𒈣𒁻 (ma₂-laḫ₄ /⁠malaḫ⁠/, “shipman, sailor”), reinterpreted in Semitic as an occupational noun from the root م ل ح (m l ḥ)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38879","headword_ar":"مُلَاحٌ","root":"mlH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maliyHN","text_ar":"مَلِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n38883","headword_ar":"مَلَّاحٌ","root":"mlH","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A seller of salt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a possessor of salt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutamal~iHN","text_ar":"مُتَمَلِّحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) which also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who provides himself with salt for travelling-provision:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a trader in salt."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mal~aAHN","text_ar":"مَلَّاحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sailor; a shipman; a seaman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mariner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K:) so called because constantly upon the salt water. (T.) ―         -b3-  Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who constantly attends to a river"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahor","text_ar":"نَهْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; in some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baHor","text_ar":"بَحْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to put its mouth into a right"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper state."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-  His occupation is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"milaAHapN","text_ar":"مِلَاحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mal~aAHiy~apN","text_ar":"مَلَّاحِيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["IAar","K","T","S"]},{"entry_id":"n38884","headword_ar":"مُلَّاحٌ","root":"mlH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maliyHN","text_ar":"مَلِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [A coll. gen. n.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoDN","text_ar":"حَمْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lth, T, S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a leguminous garden-plant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tender plant, with a salt flavour, growing in smooth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft, and depressed, tracts of land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a herb of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having twigs and leaves, growing in tracts such as are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qifaAf","text_ar":"قِفَاف"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a salt flavour, wholesome to camels and sheep:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plant like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qul~aAm","text_ar":"قُلَّام"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is a red hue, eaten with milk, bearing grain which is collected like as is that of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fav~","text_ar":"فَثّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and made into bread, and eaten:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says AHn, and he adds, I think that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thus called because of its colour; not because of its taste:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in another place he says, that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mul~aAH","text_ar":"مُلَّاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raceme of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabaAv","text_ar":"كَبَاث"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAk","text_ar":"اَرَاك"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thus called because of its taste, which is hot, as though containing salt."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Suœda baccata."},{"kind":"text","text":"Forsk., Flor., 69. (Freytag.)]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","T","M"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}